<span id="freeTextContainer5888217391277005136">The worst element of this edition is the cringe-worthy introduction by Auberon Waugh. He apologizes for the tone of this collection by Saki, when he could have instead mentioned the word &quot;satire&quot;. He is even confused by the cat&apos;s cause of death in Tobermory. <br/><br/>Of course some pieces are better than others. However some of this collection are among Saki&apos;s best and are widely anthologized (Tobermory, again).<br/><br/>In other news, there is a typo on the back cover. Such a thing rarely happens in book world. M</span>
  <span id="freeText5888217391277005136" style="display:none">The worst element of this edition is the cringe-worthy introduction by Auberon Waugh. He apologizes for the tone of this collection by Saki, when he could have instead mentioned the word "satire". He is even confused by the cat's cause of death in Tobermory. <br /><br />Of course some pieces are better than others. However some of this collection are among Saki's best and are widely anthologized (Tobermory, again).<br /><br />In other news, there is a typo on the back cover. Such a thing rarely happens in book world. Must lie down. </span>
